Date: 0/0/1956
Source: NZ Fishes: An Identification Guide
Author: GRAHAM
Vol / Page: 78
Edition:
Quote: The porbeagle [<i>Lamma Whitleyi </i> Phillips] is often called the Mackerel Shark on account of its habit of devouring so many Mackerel. It is sometimes erroneously called Mako Shark, but when the two species are seen the difference is most apparent.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Fisherman's Bible
Author: WILSON
Vol / Page: 219
Edition:
Quote: PORBEAGLE SHARK<i> Lamna nasus</i>: A swife-swimming shark similar in appearance to the mako, but not rated highly by game fishermen as it lacks the mako's superb fighting qualities. Also known as Beaumaris-shark and Mackerel-shark. Prominent in New Zealand, particularly in Cook Strait. and pelagic shark of cool to temperate waters.
Notes:

